41
00:01:34,300 --> 00:01:37,440
Euler Lagrange equations of motion for those coordinates.

42
00:01:37,880 --> 00:01:38,440
So,

43
00:01:38,440 --> 00:01:39,120
for example,

44
00:01:39,120 --> 00:01:42,080
for the particle in two dimensions,

45
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:45,700
moving around on a plane,

46
00:01:45,700 --> 00:01:52,080
we can describe its location by two coordinates.

47
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:53,660
We could use x and y,

48
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:54,180
of course.

49
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:59,240
Or we can use r and theta.

50
00:02:00,259 --> 00:02:03,380
Distance from the origin and angle from the horizontal,

51
00:02:03,380 --> 00:02:04,080
for example.

52
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,120
Then the components of velocity,

53
00:02:09,120 --> 00:02:11,870
now we could choose to describe the velocity

54
00:02:11,870 --> 00:02:14,620
by the x and y components of velocity,

55
00:02:14,620 --> 00:02:18,370
but we can also use the

56
00:02:18,370 --> 00:02:22,120
r and angular components of velocity.

57
00:02:22,620 --> 00:02:25,870
The component of velocity along the radial direction

58
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:29,120
and the component of the velocity perpendicular to it.

59
00:02:29,380 --> 00:02:33,180
To describe the velocity vector.

60
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:37,760
The component of the velocity along the radius vector,

61
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:38,960
that's just,

62
00:02:38,960 --> 00:02:40,340
let's call it v sub r,

63
00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:42,680
and that's just r dot,

64
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:44,420
the time derivative of r.

65
00:02:45,400 --> 00:02:46,960
The other component,

66
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,440
which I can call v theta,

67
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,700
let's call it v theta.

68
00:02:50,860 --> 00:02:53,540
It means the component of the velocity

69
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:56,220
in the direction perpendicular to the radius.

70
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,160
That's not theta dot.

71
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:01,420
But it's r times theta dot.

72
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:05,300
Why?

73
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:10,090
Because a given rate of change of the angle will

74
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:14,200
correspond to a larger velocity the further away you are.

75
00:03:15,180 --> 00:03:18,280
A given angular rotational velocity,

76
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,580
theta dot,

77
00:03:19,580 --> 00:03:21,910
will give you a larger overall

78
00:03:21,910 --> 00:03:24,240
velocity the further away you are,

79
00:03:24,240 --> 00:03:25,640
proportional to r.

80
00:03:26,020 --> 00:03:26,660
So,

81
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:29,360
these then are the components of the velocity vector.

82
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,760
The components of the velocity in the two directions are,

83
00:03:31,760 --> 00:03:33,520
and the perpendicular direction.

84
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:36,910
If you choose components of

85
00:03:36,910 --> 00:03:39,400
the velocity along perpendicular axes,

86
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,230
then the square of the velocity

87
00:03:41,230 --> 00:03:43,060
is just the sums of the squares.

88
00:03:43,440 --> 00:03:46,050
Sums of the squares of the components of

89
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:48,660
velocity are the magnitude of the velocity vector.

90
00:03:48,940 --> 00:03:53,170
And the kinetic energy is just one half the mass

91
00:03:53,170 --> 00:03:57,400
of the particle times v r squared plus v theta squared.

92
00:03:57,400 --> 00:04:00,650
So that just becomes r dot

93
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:03,900
squared plus r squared theta dot squared.

94
00:04:05,980 --> 00:04:06,580
Now,

95
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:07,900
just to make it more interesting,

96
00:04:07,900 --> 00:04:10,860
I also imagined that there was a potential energy,

97
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,400
but in particular,

98
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,459
a potential energy which only

99
00:04:14,459 --> 00:04:16,519
depends on distance from the origin.

100
00:04:17,019 --> 00:04:17,620
Now,

101
00:04:17,620 --> 00:04:19,200
that of course is not a law of thought.

102
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:20,000
There,

103
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,890
you could imagine potential energies

104
00:04:21,890 --> 00:04:23,780
which depend also on the angle.

105
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,380
But,

106
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:28,670
it's especially interesting in many contexts

107
00:04:28,670 --> 00:04:31,100
to study the central force problem.

108
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,910
The central force problem is the one where

109
00:04:33,910 --> 00:04:36,540
the force points toward or away from the origin,

110
00:04:37,140 --> 00:04:39,830
and is equivalent to the statement that

111
00:04:39,830 --> 00:04:42,520
the potential energy only depends on r,

112
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:43,400
and not theta.

113
00:04:43,960 --> 00:04:44,520
So,

114
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,280
let's subtract off minus u of r.

115
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,800
That's not the energy now,

116
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:50,840
that's the Lagrangian.

117
00:04:53,940 --> 00:04:54,500
Alright,

118
00:04:54,500 --> 00:04:55,220
let's work out,

119
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:55,360
let's see,

120
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:55,900
the Euler-Lagrange equations.

121
00:04:56,620 --> 00:04:58,000
Let me remind you what they are,

122
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,180
the Euler-Lagrange equations.

123
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:03,200
I'll write them in a general context first.

124
00:05:03,680 --> 00:05:08,570
We first construct the derivative of the Lagrangian with respect

125
00:05:08,570 --> 00:05:13,460
to the time derivative of any one of the coordinates.

126
00:05:14,060 --> 00:05:14,880
Let's put this,

127
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:15,740
qi,

128
00:05:15,740 --> 00:05:17,000
let's pick one of the coordinates,

129
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,180
call it qi.

130
00:05:18,620 --> 00:05:20,420
Is u of r theta?

131
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,360
No.

132
00:05:22,340 --> 00:05:23,840
I'm specializing to the special case

133
00:05:23,840 --> 00:05:25,340
where u of r is theta.

134
00:05:25,360 --> 00:05:26,460
u only depends on r.

135
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,200
As I said,

136
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:30,060
there's nothing holy about that,

137
00:05:30,240 --> 00:05:31,680
but for example,

138
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,800
it is true of gravitational forces,

139
00:05:34,100 --> 00:05:36,040
the force of the sun on the earth,

140
00:05:36,280 --> 00:05:39,090
the potential energy is only dependent

141
00:05:39,090 --> 00:05:41,900
on the distance from the sun.

142
00:05:42,180 --> 00:05:44,300
It also corresponds to a symmetry,

143
00:05:44,979 --> 00:05:47,020
corresponds to rotational symmetry,

144
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:51,760
that the potential energy does not depend on the angle,

145
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:53,520
is simply a statement

146
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,950
that the physics of the problem

147
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:58,380
is invariant under rotation of axes.

148
00:05:59,360 --> 00:06:01,380
And we'll come back to that.

149
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,080
Alright,

150
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:04,240
so for each coordinate,

151
00:06:04,540 --> 00:06:08,380
in this case the two coordinates are r and theta,

152
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:12,180
for each coordinate we begin by writing down

153
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:16,260
the canonical momentum conjugate to the coordinate.

154
00:06:16,660 --> 00:06:19,730
That means the derivative of the

155
00:06:19,730 --> 00:06:22,800
Lagrangian with respect to the velocity,

156
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:24,500
or with respect to the q dot,

157
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:28,400
with respect to the time derivative of the coordinate,

158
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:31,680
and that's called pi sub i,

159
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:34,740
and one says that pi sub i

160
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:37,480
is the momentum conjugate to q sub i.

161
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:39,100
Then,

162
00:06:39,100 --> 00:06:41,840
the Euler-Lagrange equations are that

163
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:44,580
d by dt of this object,

164
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,040
d by dt,

165
00:06:47,780 --> 00:06:51,020
sometimes I'll write just dl by dq dot,

166
00:06:51,020 --> 00:06:53,380
and sometimes I'll just write pi sub i.

167
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,680
Let's write pi sub i is

168
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:59,800
equal to the derivative of the Lagrangian

169
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:02,720
with respect to q sub i.

170
00:07:04,540 --> 00:07:08,480
We could also write this as d by dt

171
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:13,270
of the derivative of the Lagrangian

172
00:07:13,270 --> 00:07:16,680
with respect to the i-th generalized velocity,

173
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,300
q sub i dot.

174
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:21,000
That's what we got for the Lagrangian.

175
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:22,240
We got that from the principle of least action

176
00:07:22,240 --> 00:07:25,460
when we applied Euler-Lagrange method to it.

177
00:07:26,980 --> 00:07:28,780
So let's work that out now

178
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:30,580
for the two coordinates r and theta.

179
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,320
First r.

180
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:37,080
The derivative of the Lagrangian with respect to r dot,

181
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:37,580
well,

182
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:39,200
r dot only occurs here.

183
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,380
That's the only place it occurs.

184
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,440
And so we can write that pi sub r,

185
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:48,560
which is the same as the time derivative

186
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:51,000
of the derivative of the Lagrangian,

187
00:07:51,020 --> 00:07:52,120
with respect to r dot,

188
00:07:52,979 --> 00:07:54,580
that's just equal to one,

189
00:07:54,720 --> 00:07:55,880
not one half,

190
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:58,120
m r dot.

191
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:02,240
Derivative of L with respect to r dot

192
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,820
is just m r dot.

193
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:05,920
Alright,

194
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,180
so not too surprisingly,

195
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:10,100
the radial component of the momentum

196
00:08:10,100 --> 00:08:12,210
is nothing but the mass

197
00:08:12,210 --> 00:08:14,320
times the radial component of velocity.

198
00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:15,860
Not too surprising.

199
00:08:16,780 --> 00:08:19,500
And then our equation of motion becomes,

200
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:21,600
d by dt of this,

201
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,380
well,

202
00:08:22,380 --> 00:08:23,640
d by dt of this,

203
00:08:23,740 --> 00:08:25,900
that's just m r double dot.

204
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,280
The second time derivative of r.

205
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:30,720
We assume the mass is constant.

206
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,500
So the first term,

207
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:35,080
d by dt of pi sub r,

208
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:36,700
is just m r double dot,

209
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,400
and that has to equal

210
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:42,059
partial of L with respect to r.

211
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,200
Now,

212
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,260
there are two contributions to that.

213
00:08:46,940 --> 00:08:49,240
r appears in two places.

214
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:51,040
One is it appears in u.

215
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,060
That's not surprising.

216
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:55,300
But the other is that

217
00:08:55,300 --> 00:08:57,220
it appears multiplying theta dot squared.

218
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:02,940
Let's do the theta dot squared term first.

219
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:05,880
Partial of L with respect to r

220
00:09:06,640 --> 00:09:08,040
is m over 2.

221
00:09:09,219 --> 00:09:10,420
We're differentiating

222
00:09:10,420 --> 00:09:14,720
m over 2 times r squared times theta dot squared.

223
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,360
We're differentiating it with respect to r.

224
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:18,900
Alright?

225
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:25,180
So that's m r theta dot squared.

226
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:26,680
Do I have that right?

227
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:29,080
m r theta dot squared.

228
00:09:29,280 --> 00:09:30,160
That's one term,

229
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:33,780
but then the other term comes from differentiating u

230
00:09:33,780 --> 00:09:35,060
with respect to r.

231
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:38,920
And that's minus d u by d r.

232
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:41,560
Alright,

233
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:44,660
let's erase this intermediate expression here

234
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:47,000
and just look now at the equation for r.

235
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,460
What does it have?

236
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:48,660
Well,

237
00:09:48,660 --> 00:09:49,360
first of all,

238
00:09:49,360 --> 00:09:52,400
it has mass times radial component

239
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,080
of a kind of acceleration here,

240
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:55,480
r double dot.

241
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,080
But then it has,

242
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,720
first of all,

243
00:09:58,720 --> 00:09:59,200
over here,

244
00:09:59,200 --> 00:09:59,960
the force,

245
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:01,180
the u by d r,

246
00:10:01,220 --> 00:10:02,480
but then it has this extra term.

247
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,200
This extra term depends on the fact

248
00:10:07,800 --> 00:10:11,840
that the particle is moving in the theta direction.

249
00:10:12,340 --> 00:10:13,320
In other words,

250
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:16,300
it depends on the fact that there's angular velocity.

251
00:10:18,060 --> 00:10:20,200
m r theta dot squared.

252
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,960
Proportional to the square of theta dot.

253
00:10:23,680 --> 00:10:24,760
First of all,

254
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,620
it's positive.

255
00:10:27,020 --> 00:10:30,420
It looks like it's an extra contribution to the force.

256
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:32,320
We can kind of think

257
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,580
of it as an extra contribution

258
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:35,440
to the radial component of force.

259
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:40,640
It enters into the equation on the right-hand side

260
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:43,220
as if there were a positive force.

261
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,980
What does a positive force mean?

262
00:10:44,980 --> 00:10:48,620
A positive force means one radially outward.

263
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,940
So this force,

264
00:10:50,940 --> 00:10:52,300
it's not a real force.

265
00:10:52,720 --> 00:10:53,720
What's its name?

266
00:10:54,240 --> 00:10:57,180
I called it Coriolis last time because I was tired.

267
00:10:57,320 --> 00:10:58,280
What's the right name for it?

268
00:10:58,840 --> 00:10:59,480
Centrifugal.

269
00:10:59,900 --> 00:11:04,000
This is the centrifugal force on the particle

270
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:08,200
which has the apparent effect

271
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:12,460
of creating a repulsion away from the center.

272
00:11:14,080 --> 00:11:14,960
We're all familiar with the idea

273
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:15,220
of centrifugal force.

274
00:11:15,220 --> 00:11:15,620
We're all familiar with it.

275
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:19,380
And here's its mathematical origin.

276
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:23,540
It comes from differentiating L with respect to r,

277
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:28,980
but the piece of it which multiplies theta dot squared.

278
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:31,100
So we don't have to...

279
00:11:32,819 --> 00:11:36,420
The Lagrangian method is a mindless method.

280
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:38,580
It requires zero intelligence.

281
00:11:38,980 --> 00:11:40,740
You just follow the steps.

282
00:11:40,980 --> 00:11:42,480
Write down L.

283
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:45,200
Write down the L by dq dot.

284
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:47,560
Differentiate it with respect to time

285
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:49,580
and set it equal to the L by dq.

