00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:21,960
get rid of the word real and really and actually

300
00:12:21,960 --> 00:12:23,760
and really and all those words.

301
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:24,520
Nothing.

302
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:25,440
I didn't mean anything.

303
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:29,140
It's on the right-hand side of the equation.

304
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:30,360
There it is.

305
00:12:30,860 --> 00:12:32,520
What is it you used to mean?

306
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,940
What I simply meant is it doesn't come from

307
00:12:38,940 --> 00:12:40,460
the derivative of a potential energy.

308
00:12:40,640 --> 00:12:41,280
That's all.

309
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:46,280
It is part of what is called the generalized force.

310
00:12:49,920 --> 00:12:56,140
And I withdraw the real.

311
00:12:58,020 --> 00:12:58,720
What's that?

312
00:12:59,960 --> 00:13:01,710
That it's a term that arises

313
00:13:01,710 --> 00:13:03,460
because of the choice of the origin.

314
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:04,660
Well,

315
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:06,260
yes.

316
00:13:07,460 --> 00:13:08,160
Yes.

317
00:13:09,779 --> 00:13:11,180
But nevertheless,

318
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:14,980
in some sense it's as real as anything else.

319
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,180
Let's go on.

320
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:18,090
Let's not belabor the issue

321
00:13:18,090 --> 00:13:19,900
of whether it's a real force.

322
00:13:20,060 --> 00:13:22,080
It occurs on the right-hand side of the equation.

323
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:24,570
It tends to have the effect of

324
00:13:24,570 --> 00:13:26,680
keeping the particle away from the origin.

325
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,540
And that's not surprising.

326
00:13:28,840 --> 00:13:31,720
If a particle is moving with an angular velocity,

327
00:13:32,640 --> 00:13:35,480
it doesn't want to pass through the origin.

328
00:13:35,680 --> 00:13:36,240
But here it is.

329
00:13:36,420 --> 00:13:37,260
Centrifugal force.

330
00:13:37,980 --> 00:13:38,500
Okay,

331
00:13:38,500 --> 00:13:39,340
let's write down,

332
00:13:39,340 --> 00:13:40,400
as Michael said,

333
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:42,820
let's write down now the equation for theta.

334
00:13:44,199 --> 00:13:46,580
So let's figure out what pi sub theta is.

335
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,520
Pi sub theta,

336
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,880
let's do it over here.

337
00:13:50,420 --> 00:13:51,880
Pi sub theta,

338
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,750
that's the derivative of the

339
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,620
Lagrangian with respect to theta dot.

340
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:59,020
Notice theta dot squared appears.

341
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,600
So we have to differentiate theta dot squared.

342
00:14:02,060 --> 00:14:04,740
And the result is m over 2.

343
00:14:05,140 --> 00:14:05,560
No,

344
00:14:05,560 --> 00:14:07,720
the 2 goes away because theta dot squared,

345
00:14:07,900 --> 00:14:09,020
when we differentiate it,

346
00:14:09,020 --> 00:14:10,880
gets rid of the 2.

347
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:15,780
m r squared theta dot.

348
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,300
Differentiate theta dot squared,

349
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:19,900
and you get twice theta dot.

350
00:14:20,140 --> 00:14:24,900
The 2 eats up the 2 in the kinetic energy.

351
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:27,420
That's pi sub theta.

352
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:32,100
Now let's write down the equation for pi sub theta.

353
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:37,480
It's d by dt of pi sub theta.

354
00:14:37,880 --> 00:14:39,000
That's d by dt of pi sub theta.

355
00:14:39,020 --> 00:14:44,140
That's d by dt of m r squared theta dot.

356
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:45,840
The whole thing.

357
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,680
That's equal to what?

358
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,180
That's equal to the derivative of

359
00:14:52,180 --> 00:14:54,280
the Lagrangian with respect to theta.

360
00:14:57,280 --> 00:14:59,020
dL by d theta.

361
00:15:00,120 --> 00:15:00,600
Well,

362
00:15:00,600 --> 00:15:01,780
take a look at that Lagrangian.

363
00:15:01,860 --> 00:15:02,960
Do you see theta in it anywhere?

364
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:03,660
I don't.

365
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:05,280
I see r.

366
00:15:05,920 --> 00:15:07,040
I see r dot.

367
00:15:07,040 --> 00:15:08,000
I see theta dot.

368
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:09,240
But I don't see theta.

369
00:15:10,540 --> 00:15:13,130
The consequence or the fact that

370
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:15,720
theta doesn't appear in the Lagrangian

371
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:18,720
is a consequence in this case of the

372
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:21,720
rotational invariance of the problem that I set up.

373
00:15:22,420 --> 00:15:24,340
Nothing depends on that angle.

374
00:15:24,560 --> 00:15:25,660
In particular,

375
00:15:25,660 --> 00:15:28,880
the potential energy doesn't depend on angle.

376
00:15:29,340 --> 00:15:29,940
Therefore,

377
00:15:29,940 --> 00:15:32,140
dL by d theta is equal to 0.

378
00:15:32,780 --> 00:15:33,600
In other words,

379
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:36,500
rotational symmetry of the problem tells us that

380
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:37,920
the right-hand side is 0.

381
00:15:41,680 --> 00:15:42,240
Now,

382
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,220
I could work this out in detail,

383
00:15:44,220 --> 00:15:46,140
but why bother?

384
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:50,570
Why bother since I know that what this equation says

385
00:15:50,570 --> 00:15:54,340
is that m r squared theta dot is a constant.

386
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,480
Let's just use it in that form.

387
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,160
It's a constant,

388
00:15:58,160 --> 00:16:00,300
and that means there's a conservation law.

389
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:02,500
What is this quantity called,

390
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,700
m r squared theta dot?

391
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:11,280
It's the momentum canonically conjugate to theta.

392
00:16:11,520 --> 00:16:12,380
But of course,

393
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:13,260
it's the angular momentum.

394
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:15,700
It's the angular momentum,

395
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:18,520
m r squared theta dot.

396
00:16:18,940 --> 00:16:21,020
The symbol that's usually used

397
00:16:21,020 --> 00:16:23,100
for angular momentum is capital L.

398
00:16:24,120 --> 00:16:26,870
And so instead of fiddling around with

399
00:16:26,870 --> 00:16:29,620
this equation and doing something complicated with it,

400
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:33,000
we can simply say that m r squared,

401
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:37,560
theta dot is equal to the angular momentum,

402
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:38,700
which is constant.

403
00:16:39,440 --> 00:16:39,720
Now,

404
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:40,500
how big is it?

405
00:16:40,780 --> 00:16:42,740
That depends on the starting point.

406
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:44,500
That depends on the initial conditions.

407
00:16:45,460 --> 00:16:47,180
If you know the initial condition,

408
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:48,240
for example,

409
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:49,740
if you know r and theta

410
00:16:49,740 --> 00:16:51,240
and r dot and theta dot initially,

411
00:16:51,859 --> 00:16:54,740
then you know the angular momentum forever after,

412
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,740
because it doesn't change.

413
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,700
That's not true of m r dot,

414
00:17:00,700 --> 00:17:02,300
pi sub r.

415
00:17:02,300 --> 00:17:04,230
It does change because of the

416
00:17:04,230 --> 00:17:06,160
force and because of the centrifugal force.

417
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:09,119
But the angular momentum does not change.

418
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,099
It's constant,

419
00:17:10,099 --> 00:17:12,599
and that's what the equation of motion says.

420
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:13,520
So again,

421
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:15,349
this is an example of a symmetry

422
00:17:15,349 --> 00:17:17,180
telling us that there's a conservation law.

423
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:19,319
And once we know it,

424
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:21,859
we can treat L as a constant.

425
00:17:23,180 --> 00:17:24,930
A constant which is given

426
00:17:24,930 --> 00:17:26,680
to us by the initial conditions.

427
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:28,140
For example,

428
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:29,420
that now means,

429
00:17:29,420 --> 00:17:32,020
let's come over to this half of the blackboard,

430
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:34,660
that allows us to solve for theta dot,

431
00:17:35,660 --> 00:17:37,460
and it's equal to the angular

432
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:39,260
momentum divided by m r squared.

433
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:42,540
Well,

434
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,180
that's interesting.

435
00:17:43,480 --> 00:17:46,260
Now we can come back to the equation for r.

436
00:17:46,620 --> 00:17:48,520
Let's come back to the equation for r.

437
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:52,040
Now that we know something about theta dot,

438
00:17:52,660 --> 00:17:55,260
let's plug it into the equation for r.

439
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,000
And what do we get?

440
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:58,300
We get an equation for r,

441
00:17:58,300 --> 00:18:00,900
which is m r double dot,

442
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:02,560
is equal,

443
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:05,200
now let me first begin writing minus du dr.

444
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:07,700
Minus du dr,

445
00:18:07,700 --> 00:18:11,280
that's of course the familiar piece.

446
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:12,540
And then,

447
00:18:12,540 --> 00:18:13,860
let's work it out,

448
00:18:13,860 --> 00:18:17,400
plus m r,

449
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,100
and now theta dot squared.

450
00:18:19,520 --> 00:18:20,460
Where's theta dot?

451
00:18:20,460 --> 00:18:20,880
Here it is,

452
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:21,260
right here.

453
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:23,200
L squared,

454
00:18:25,699 --> 00:18:30,100
divided by m squared r to the fourth.

455
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,560
I've squared theta dot,

456
00:18:32,780 --> 00:18:34,980
that gives me l squared divided

457
00:18:34,980 --> 00:18:37,180
by m squared r to the fourth.

458
00:18:37,540 --> 00:18:41,440
Let's cancel out the unnecessary symbols.

459
00:18:42,540 --> 00:18:44,920
m cancels against m squared,

460
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,360
to give one power of m in the denominator.

461
00:18:48,500 --> 00:18:51,180
And r cancels against r fourth,

462
00:18:51,500 --> 00:18:54,920
to give three powers of r in the denominator.

463
00:18:55,560 --> 00:18:56,700
r cubed.

464
00:18:59,520 --> 00:19:01,140
l is a constant.

465
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:02,940
Once we fixed it,

466
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:03,580
we fixed it.

467
00:19:03,860 --> 00:19:04,980
And the effect,

468
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:08,480
the entire effect of the centrifugal force,

469
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:11,040
is now to tell us that effectively,

470
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:13,570
there's a force on this particle

471
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:15,340
pushing it away from the origin,

472
00:19:15,540 --> 00:19:17,080
that's the plus sign here,

473
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:19,710
proportional to one divided by

474
00:19:19,710 --> 00:19:21,640
the distance from the origin cubed.

475
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:25,080
Also proportional to the square of the angular momentum,

476
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:27,200
and also the inverse mass.

477
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:30,020
Okay?

478
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:30,520
So,

479
00:19:30,520 --> 00:19:32,260
this,

480
00:19:32,260 --> 00:19:32,860
again,

481
00:19:32,860 --> 00:19:33,360
of course,

482
00:19:33,360 --> 00:19:35,100
this is nothing but the centrifugal force.

483
00:19:36,060 --> 00:19:38,620
And notice that once you know the angular momentum,

484
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:41,060
once you've fixed it by knowing

485
00:19:41,060 --> 00:19:43,240
the initial motion of the system,

486
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:47,700
then the effect of the rotational or the angular coordinate

487
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:50,520
is to simply set up the centrifugal force,

488
00:19:50,620 --> 00:19:53,320
which is like one divided by the distance cubed.

489
00:19:53,620 --> 00:19:55,060
It gets very strong,

490
00:19:55,679 --> 00:19:57,860
when the distance from the origin gets small.

491
00:19:59,300 --> 00:20:01,560
When the particle has angular momentum,

492
00:20:01,840 --> 00:20:03,740
it does not want to get near the origin.

493
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,420
It's pushed away from the origin

494
00:20:05,420 --> 00:20:06,920
with a one over r cubed force.

495
00:20:07,600 --> 00:20:08,400
Far away,

496
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:10,140
when you're far away,

497
00:20:10,260 --> 00:20:11,820
this one over r cubed gets small,

498
00:20:11,960 --> 00:20:13,380
and it's not so important.

499
00:20:13,600 --> 00:20:13,700
Yeah?

500
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:14,840
So,

501
00:20:14,840 --> 00:20:16,560
I've already been taught that

502
00:20:17,600 --> 00:20:20,200
centrifugal force is actually just the effect of inertia,

503
00:20:20,420 --> 00:20:21,660
trying to take the energy of the...

504
00:20:21,660 --> 00:20:22,000
Is what?

505
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:22,420
Is what?

506
00:20:22,420 --> 00:20:22,700
Is...

507
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:23,420
Is it?

508
00:20:23,420 --> 00:20:24,140
Is it the effect of inertia,

509
00:20:24,140 --> 00:20:26,140
trying to take the energy of the straight line?

510
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:27,440
Is that not?

511
00:20:27,580 --> 00:20:28,780
It is true.

512
00:20:29,580 --> 00:20:30,200
Of course,

513
00:20:30,200 --> 00:20:31,760
there are many ways to say the same thing.

514
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,480
It...

515
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:40,320
If a particle has some angular momentum...

516
00:20:40,320 --> 00:20:41,580
First of all,

517
00:20:41,580 --> 00:20:42,840
if it has some angular momentum,

518
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,460
it means it has some theta dot.

519
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,360
So that means it's not pointed,

520
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:50,060
its velocity is not pointed right toward the center.

521
00:20:51,340 --> 00:20:54,140
If the velocity is not pointed right toward the center,

522
00:20:57,439 --> 00:20:59,620
then what this is telling you is,

523
00:20:59,620 --> 00:21:00,760
roughly speaking,

524
00:21:00,860 --> 00:21:01,080
yeah,

525
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:02,720
it wants to move along a straight line.

526
00:21:02,860 --> 00:21:04,020
If it moves along a straight line,

527
00:21:04,180 --> 00:21:05,660
it never gets too close to the origin.

528
00:21:06,240 --> 00:21:07,700
But it's telling you more than that.

529
00:21:07,980 --> 00:21:10,740
It's telling you even a rather powerful force,

530
00:21:10,800 --> 00:21:12,340
unless it's strong enough to

531
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:13,880
overcome this one over r cubed.

532
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,160
And one over r cubed is very,

533
00:21:16,160 --> 00:21:17,380
very strong at the origin.

534
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:18,100
For example,

535
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:19,460
the...

536
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:22,220
the gravitational force,

537
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,740
or the Coulomb force between charged particles,

538
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:25,760
is one over r squared.

539
00:21:26,140 --> 00:21:29,920
One over r cubed is much stronger at small distances

540
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,680
than one over r squared.

541
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:34,520
So this is the dominant thing at small distances.

542
00:21:34,940 --> 00:21:38,160
And it tells you that this particle will not crash,

543
00:21:38,420 --> 00:21:40,540
that the Earth will not crash into the Sun,

544
00:21:40,700 --> 00:21:42,560
as long as it has some angular momentum.

545
00:21:43,680 --> 00:21:44,200
Okay.

546
00:21:44,740 --> 00:21:45,260
Well...

547
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:49,480
That's the idea of centrifugal force.

548
00:21:49,660 --> 00:21:50,040
And...

549
00:21:50,060 --> 00:21:52,640
And the main reason I bring it up,

550
00:21:52,640 --> 00:21:53,060
two reasons.

551
00:21:53,200 --> 00:21:53,700
First of all,

552
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,420
to give you an example

553
00:21:55,420 --> 00:21:57,160
of how to use Lagrange's equations,

554
00:21:57,940 --> 00:22:00,960
the mindless application of Lagrange's equations,

555
00:22:01,920 --> 00:22:04,400
and to give you an example of symmetry

556
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:08,440
and how it acts to create a conserved quantity.

557
00:22:09,740 --> 00:22:10,460
All right.

558
00:22:10,460 --> 00:22:10,620
Now,

559
00:22:10,620 --> 00:22:11,760
just some...

560
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,100
It's not really mathematics,

561
00:22:14,220 --> 00:22:18,580
just some notation that you'll see over and over again.

562
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,140
Supposing you have a function of a lot of variables.

563
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:23,580
And the problem is,

564
00:22:23,580 --> 00:22:24,040
for example,

565
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:24,960
to minimize it.

566
00:22:26,300 --> 00:22:26,780
Sometimes...

567
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,780
Let's call the variables,

568
00:22:29,020 --> 00:22:30,360
let's give them a generic name,

569
00:22:30,640 --> 00:22:31,820
alpha sub i.

570
00:22:32,580 --> 00:22:33,800
I'm mixing up...

571
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,800
I'm using lots of letters of the alphabet

572
00:22:35,800 --> 00:22:39,500
just to help you learn the Greek alphabet.

573
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:42,680
All right.

574
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:44,620
So let's suppose we have a whole bunch of...

575
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,880
They're not coordinates of any particle or anything.

576
00:22:48,020 --> 00:22:48,880
They're just a bunch of variables.

577
00:22:48,880 --> 00:22:51,440
And we have some function which depends on them.

578
00:22:53,580 --> 00:22:57,680
The rule for finding the minimum of the function

579
00:22:57,680 --> 00:22:59,410
is that the derivative of f

580
00:22:59,410 --> 00:23:01,140
with respect to all of the alphas

581
00:23:01,140 --> 00:23:02,120
should be equal to zero.

582
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:08,700
Sometimes you'll see that stated as delta f equals zero.

583
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:12,600
Sometimes I'm going to state things in that form.

584
00:23:12,760 --> 00:23:13,660
Let me tell you what that means.

585
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:16,020
Delta f means...

586
00:23:16,020 --> 00:23:17,410
It means that if you're

587
00:23:17,410 --> 00:23:18,800
at the minimum of a function,

588
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:20,920
let's say the minimum is over here,

589
00:23:21,000 --> 00:23:22,280
if you happen to be at the minimum,

590
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:26,540
then a small change in alpha...

591
00:23:26,540 --> 00:23:29,600
Let's move a small change in all of the alphas.

592
00:23:29,800 --> 00:23:31,460
You move from one point to another.

593
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:34,520
This little displacement is just delta alpha,

594
00:23:34,520 --> 00:23:35,420
let's call it.

595
00:23:36,060 --> 00:23:37,100
Delta alpha one,

596
00:23:37,100 --> 00:23:38,080
delta alpha two,

597
00:23:38,080 --> 00:23:39,280
delta alpha all of them.

598
00:23:42,580 --> 00:23:44,860
What delta alpha equals zero says

599
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:47,980
is that if you move away from the minimum,

600
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:52,480
the function doesn't change to first order.

601
00:23:52,660 --> 00:23:54,700
To first order in small variables.

602
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,760
How do we see that?

603
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:57,720
Well,

604
00:23:57,720 --> 00:24:00,460
if we calculate the small change in a function

605
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:03,070
as we move from a point alpha

606
00:24:03,070 --> 00:24:05,680
to a point alpha plus delta alpha,

607
00:24:05,980 --> 00:24:07,420
what happens to the function?

608
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:11,860
The change in the function is the derivative of f

609
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:17,320
with respect to alpha i times delta alpha i,

610
00:24:18,180 --> 00:24:19,360
summed over i.

611
00:24:20,600 --> 00:24:21,780
In other words,

612
00:24:21,780 --> 00:24:23,600
as you move from one point to another,

613
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,530
you get a contribution from

614
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:27,360
each one of the partial derivatives.

615
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:31,900
If you change the arguments of a function,

616
00:24:32,100 --> 00:24:34,740
the function changes to first order,

617
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:38,360
ignoring things of order alpha squared,

618
00:24:38,360 --> 00:24:39,280
alpha cubed,

619
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:40,000
and so forth,

620
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:43,440
which are much smaller than delta alpha,

621
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:47,240
ignoring things of scale,

622
00:24:47,320 --> 00:24:48,360
delta alpha squared,

623
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:49,280
delta alpha cubed,

624
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:49,940
and so forth,

625
00:24:50,060 --> 00:24:52,120
the change in the function to first order

626
00:24:52,120 --> 00:24:54,580
is just the derivative of f with respect to alpha

627
00:24:54,580 --> 00:24:56,060
times the change in alpha,

628
00:24:56,240 --> 00:24:59,360
summed over all of the variables.

629
00:25:00,540 --> 00:25:01,060
Okay?

630
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:06,560
To say that delta f is equal to zero,

631
00:25:07,500 --> 00:25:09,520
for any delta alpha,

632
00:25:09,520 --> 00:25:11,500
no matter which way you move,

633
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:14,020
is the same as saying that all

634
00:25:14,020 --> 00:25:16,000
of these partial derivatives are equal to zero.

635
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:18,900
The only way that this can be equal to zero

636
00:25:18,900 --> 00:25:21,040
for all possible variations,

637
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:25,340
the delta alphas are called the variation of alpha,

638
00:25:25,520 --> 00:25:27,540
for all possible variations,

639
00:25:27,780 --> 00:25:28,380
in other words,

640
00:25:28,380 --> 00:25:30,580
no matter what direction in this space you move,

641
00:25:32,100 --> 00:25:33,740
to say that you're at a minimum,

642
00:25:33,980 --> 00:25:37,100
to say that f doesn't change except to higher order,

643
00:25:37,300 --> 00:25:38,990
is the same as saying the f

644
00:25:38,990 --> 00:25:40,680
by d alpha is equal to zero

645
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:42,740
for each one of the alpha i's.

646
00:25:43,780 --> 00:25:44,300
Okay?

647
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:44,820
So,

648
00:25:44,820 --> 00:25:47,200
these say the same thing,

649
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:50,280
that derivative of f with respect to alpha

650
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:54,400
for all alpha's equals zero

651
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:56,680
is the same thing as saying

652
00:25:57,840 --> 00:26:01,940
that the variation of f is equal to zero

653
00:26:02,879 --> 00:26:04,960
when you change alpha a little bit.

654
00:26:05,140 --> 00:26:08,100
This is shorthand for the

655
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:11,060
collection of these equations over here.

656
00:26:12,140 --> 00:26:12,780
Variation,

657
00:26:12,780 --> 00:26:13,700
one says,

658
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:15,840
the variation of f is equal to zero.

659
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:17,520
As an example,

660
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:21,100
we studied the principle of least action.

661
00:26:22,980 --> 00:26:23,980
Here's a trajectory.

662
00:26:25,740 --> 00:26:28,480
And what we wrote was that the change,

663
00:26:28,720 --> 00:26:30,160
that the action is a minimum

664
00:26:30,940 --> 00:26:32,740
with respect to any variation,

665
00:26:33,100 --> 00:26:35,820
and one way of writing that is just to say

666
00:26:35,820 --> 00:26:37,420
that the change in the action

667
00:26:38,080 --> 00:26:41,160
with respect to a small change in the trajectory,

668
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:45,240
make a small change in the trajectory,

669
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:48,180
the variation of the action is equal to zero.

670
00:26:48,820 --> 00:26:50,410
That's another way of saying

671
00:26:50,410 --> 00:26:52,000
that the action is a minimum

672
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:55,280
with respect to variations of the trajectory

673
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:58,120
away from the actual trajectory.

674
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,420
That's just a notational,

675
00:27:02,639 --> 00:27:04,000
a notational,

676
00:27:06,659 --> 00:27:08,280
a notational notation.

677
00:27:12,580 --> 00:27:13,260
Okay.

678
00:27:13,260 --> 00:27:14,620
Now we want to get

679
00:27:14,620 --> 00:27:15,980
to the heart of tonight's lecture,

680
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:18,980
which is the connection between symmetries

681
00:27:19,860 --> 00:27:21,360
and conservation laws.

682
00:27:21,640 --> 00:27:23,780
We talked about it a bit up till now.

683
00:27:24,480 --> 00:27:28,160
I gave you the examples of rotational symmetry,

684
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:30,080
which we'll do in greater depth,

685
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:31,860
translational symmetry,

686
00:27:32,140 --> 00:27:35,140
but there can be other more complex symmetries,

687
00:27:35,840 --> 00:27:38,300
which I won't be very specific about,

688
00:27:38,580 --> 00:27:39,760
but will be more general.

689
00:27:40,860 --> 00:27:41,540
All right.

690
00:27:41,580 --> 00:27:43,240
Let's erase the slide.

691
00:27:43,260 --> 00:27:43,860
I'll just use this blackboard.

692
00:27:53,020 --> 00:27:55,180
The idea of a symmetry

693
00:27:55,180 --> 00:27:58,200
is a change that you can make

694
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:01,560
in the system that doesn't affect the action.

695
00:28:01,840 --> 00:28:03,000
For example,

696
00:28:03,960 --> 00:28:06,780
if we have some system of particles moving around

697
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:10,800
and the particles are interacting with each other,

698
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,240
but not interacting with some external

699
00:28:13,260 --> 00:28:13,600
object,

700
00:28:14,439 --> 00:28:17,560
then if we take the whole system,

701
00:28:17,840 --> 00:28:20,000
including its entire motion,

702
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:23,120
and we replace it by a corresponding system

703
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:24,740
that's been shifted a little bit,

704
00:28:25,520 --> 00:28:27,500
shifted over by a small amount,

705
00:28:27,720 --> 00:28:29,320
small or large for that matter,

706
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,940
then the action won't change.

707
00:28:32,340 --> 00:28:33,020
Why?

708
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:35,420
Because the action doesn't depend

709
00:28:35,420 --> 00:28:39,560
on the location of the individual objects,

710
00:28:39,720 --> 00:28:41,360
but only their relative location.

711
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:42,820
That's an assumption,

712
00:28:42,820 --> 00:28:43,300
of course.

713
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:45,460
But more than an assumption,

714
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:47,720
it defines the notion of symmetry

715
00:28:47,720 --> 00:28:49,260
under translation,

716
00:28:49,660 --> 00:28:51,680
that the action doesn't change

717
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,220
when you translate the system.

718
00:28:54,080 --> 00:28:55,360
Another example

719
00:28:55,360 --> 00:28:57,840
is pick an origin

720
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:00,960
and rotate everything relative to that origin

721
00:29:00,960 --> 00:29:02,639
by the same angle.

722
00:29:03,100 --> 00:29:05,660
Move all the particles by the same angle,

723
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:08,440
start the system over,

724
00:29:08,600 --> 00:29:09,460
again,

725
00:29:09,460 --> 00:29:11,880
the action for a given trajectory,

726
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:14,560
if we displace the entire trajectory,

727
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:16,000
will not change

728
00:29:16,780 --> 00:29:18,140
as a consequence,

729
00:29:18,480 --> 00:29:19,540
under the assumption,

730
00:29:19,820 --> 00:29:21,400
or as a consequence of the idea

731
00:29:21,400 --> 00:29:24,940
that the system is invariant

732
00:29:24,940 --> 00:29:26,720
under rotational transformations.

733
00:29:28,640 --> 00:29:29,280
Okay?

734
00:29:29,380 --> 00:29:29,960
So,

735
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:30,700
basically,

736
00:29:30,860 --> 00:29:32,740
a symmetry is an operation

737
00:29:32,740 --> 00:29:34,300
that you can do on a system,

738
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:37,100
a change that you can make in the coordinates

739
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:39,080
that doesn't affect the action.

740
00:29:46,040 --> 00:29:47,220
And in particular,

741
00:29:47,940 --> 00:29:49,920
I'm interested in a kind of symmetry

742
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:52,020
which is called an infinitesimal symmetry,

743
00:29:52,400 --> 00:29:54,500
a small change in a system.

744
00:29:54,740 --> 00:29:56,560
You can build any change

745
00:29:56,560 --> 00:29:57,660
out of small changes.

746
00:29:57,880 --> 00:29:58,500
For example,

747
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,080
if I want to rotate a system

748
00:30:00,080 --> 00:30:01,280
by 180 degrees,

749
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:03,980
I can think of it as being built up

750
00:30:03,980 --> 00:30:05,620
by a lot of little transformations,

751
00:30:05,880 --> 00:30:07,220
each of which is a rotation

752
00:30:07,220 --> 00:30:08,360
by a small angle.

753
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:11,700
Another possibility is translation,

754
00:30:12,120 --> 00:30:13,640
where if I want to say

755
00:30:13,640 --> 00:30:15,340
that a system is invariant

756
00:30:15,340 --> 00:30:16,960
under being translated by a meter,

757
00:30:17,180 --> 00:30:19,600
I can say it's invariant

758
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:20,800
under an operation

759
00:30:20,800 --> 00:30:22,320
of translating it by a centimeter,

760
00:30:22,620 --> 00:30:23,780
but do it 100 times.

761
00:30:24,700 --> 00:30:25,320
Okay?

762
00:30:25,420 --> 00:30:27,500
So it's sufficient in most cases

763
00:30:27,500 --> 00:30:29,060
to understand the effect

764
00:30:29,060 --> 00:30:32,500
of small transformations,

765
00:30:32,840 --> 00:30:34,740
transformations which only displace

766
00:30:34,740 --> 00:30:35,900
a system a little bit.

767
00:30:36,500 --> 00:30:37,700
In other words,

768
00:30:37,700 --> 00:30:39,220
working to first order

769
00:30:39,220 --> 00:30:40,180
in small quantities.

770
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:41,920
All right,

771
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:43,440
so let's define now,

772
00:30:43,540 --> 00:30:44,220
first of all,

773
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:46,560
a transformation on a system.

774
00:30:47,780 --> 00:30:49,360
It's a change in the coordinates.

775
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:51,440
Under a transformation,

776
00:30:52,220 --> 00:30:52,820
coordinates,

777
00:30:52,820 --> 00:30:54,240
let's say q sub i,

778
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,320
change to q sub i

779
00:30:57,320 --> 00:30:59,340
plus something small.

780
00:30:59,520 --> 00:31:01,420
Let epsilon be a small number

781
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:07,100
times some function i of q.

782
00:31:12,720 --> 00:31:14,500
When I say f sub i of q,

783
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,720
I mean that f sub i can depend

784
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,280
on all of the q's.

785
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:20,840
It's a little displacement

786
00:31:20,840 --> 00:31:21,640
of the system.

787
00:31:22,700 --> 00:31:25,140
If here is your configuration space,

788
00:31:25,480 --> 00:31:26,000
q1,

789
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:26,960
q2,

790
00:31:26,960 --> 00:31:27,780
so forth,

791
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:30,100
then wherever you happen to be,

792
00:31:30,980 --> 00:31:32,500
the transformation defines

793
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:33,600
a little displacement

794
00:31:33,600 --> 00:31:35,100
to a new location.

795
00:31:35,620 --> 00:31:37,400
That displacement in general

796
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:38,740
can depend on where you are,

797
00:31:38,860 --> 00:31:39,600
where you start.

798
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:45,220
But it's a small transformation,

799
00:31:45,580 --> 00:31:46,800
small in the sense that

800
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:48,380
epsilon is a small quantity

801
00:31:48,380 --> 00:31:50,460
and will keep track of things

802
00:31:50,460 --> 00:31:51,360
to order epsilon.

803
00:31:52,540 --> 00:31:53,240
All right,

804
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:54,020
so it's a displacement

805
00:31:54,020 --> 00:31:54,780
of the system,

806
00:31:54,900 --> 00:31:57,180
but not necessarily a displacement

807
00:31:57,180 --> 00:31:58,160
along an axis,

808
00:31:59,240 --> 00:32:00,940
some more complicated kind

809
00:32:00,940 --> 00:32:01,420
of displacement.

810
00:32:01,740 --> 00:32:03,080
A rotation would be an example.

811
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,380
A rotation,

812
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:05,520
in the case of a rotation,

813
00:32:05,800 --> 00:32:07,680
if I were to just use x and y,

814
00:32:07,700 --> 00:32:12,020
the change in x will depend

815
00:32:12,020 --> 00:32:12,860
on where you are.

816
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:13,580
For example,

817
00:32:13,580 --> 00:32:14,920
the change in x over here

818
00:32:14,920 --> 00:32:16,720
is different than the change

819
00:32:16,720 --> 00:32:17,760
in x over here,

820
00:32:19,820 --> 00:32:20,880
and over here,

821
00:32:21,780 --> 00:32:22,960
if the system is,

822
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:24,580
if the transformation is a rotation.

823
00:32:25,020 --> 00:32:26,620
If we're rotating the system,

824
00:32:26,780 --> 00:32:27,940
then the change in x,

825
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:29,260
which is positive over here

826
00:32:29,260 --> 00:32:31,080
and negative over here,

827
00:32:31,160 --> 00:32:32,300
depends on where you are.

828
00:32:32,580 --> 00:32:36,160
But a well-defined notion

829
00:32:36,920 --> 00:32:37,680
of a system

830
00:32:37,700 --> 00:32:39,300
is a small displacement of a system

831
00:32:39,300 --> 00:32:41,660
where the displacement of each coordinate

832
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,420
depends in some specific way

833
00:32:43,420 --> 00:32:45,000
on all of the coordinates.

834
00:32:45,480 --> 00:32:47,360
So this is a collection of functions,

835
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:48,640
one for each direction.

836
00:32:49,800 --> 00:32:51,460
And what does it mean to say

837
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,460
that we have a symmetry?

838
00:32:54,080 --> 00:32:55,740
The statement of symmetry is

839
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:58,100
that if we do such a transformation

840
00:32:58,100 --> 00:32:59,360
to the system,

841
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:02,100
that the action of a trajectory

842
00:33:02,100 --> 00:33:03,380
doesn't change.

843
00:33:04,060 --> 00:33:04,820
All right,

844
00:33:04,820 --> 00:33:06,000
the action of a trajectory

845
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:06,880
doesn't change

846
00:33:07,700 --> 00:33:09,160
if every coordinate is displaced

847
00:33:09,160 --> 00:33:10,360
in exactly this way.

848
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:13,500
That's the meaning of the term symmetry.

849
00:33:15,399 --> 00:33:17,260
What are the consequences of a symmetry?

850
00:33:22,480 --> 00:33:24,340
Which part of it?

851
00:33:28,320 --> 00:33:29,840
All right.

852
00:33:30,180 --> 00:33:32,400
A symmetry is a transformation

853
00:33:33,940 --> 00:33:35,460
which takes

854
00:33:35,460 --> 00:33:37,560
the coordinates of a system

855
00:33:37,700 --> 00:33:39,080
and displaces them a little bit

856
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:41,460
depending on where you began.

857
00:33:42,400 --> 00:33:43,080
All right.

858
00:33:43,120 --> 00:33:44,920
I'll give you some examples.

859
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,480
